                 SWITCHING BETWEEN ANALOG AND DIGITAL JOYSTICK:
                  ANALOG:
		       Press the "FIRE" button on the ANALOG joystick.
                       This activates the "PC1" light on the AMIGA Smart Port
                       and puts the hardware in analog mode.

                  DIGITAL:
                       Press the "Fire" Button on the DIGITAL joystick
                       to switch off the "PC1" light.  This deactivates the
                       analog mode of the AMIGA Smart Port hardware.

                  NOTE: The BOP Upgrade software will follow the AMIGA Smart
                        Port mode by switching from analog to digital as
                        the hardware does.


******************************************************************************
* Birds of Prey - DETAILED PRE-FLIGHT CHECK LIST (after entering cockpit)     *
*               (performed on first start-up and as needed)                   *
* Best is before take off. May be done at any time and repeated as necessary. *
******************************************************************************
IMPORTANT: The analog joystick will not function, if the light labeled "PC1"
           on the AMIGA Smart Port is not on.


IMPORTANT: You must set the center and full scale for the joystick at least
           once at the beginning of the game. (See below) This can be repeated
           as often as necessary.


USING THE ANALOG JOYSTICK:
1. Connect an analog joystick to the AMIGA Smart Port.
2. Place Port 2 of the Amiga Smart Port in analog mode by pressing the analog
   joystick "FIRE" button. (The "PC 1" light will be on)
3. The "PC1" light on the AMIGA SMART PORT should be on.
4. Make sure the analog joystick is in the center then press the "0" key to
   set the joystick center.
5. Move the joystick to all four corners of its travel to set maximum
   scale.

